HEADWORD: Roorbach
<hw>Roor"bach</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A defamatory forgery or falsehood published for
purposes of political intrigue.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The word originated in the election canvass of 1844,
when such a forgery was published, to the detriment of James K. Polk, a
candidate for President, purporting to be an extract from the
⟦ldquo⟧Travels of Baron <xex>Roorbach</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

